article.headline: Oklahoma 86, Louisiana Tech 59
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Dionnah Jackson had 18 points and 10
rebounds to lead Oklahoma to an 86-59 victory over Louisiana Tech
in the Nike Classic Saturday at the University of Oregon's McArthur
Court.

Erin Higgins led all scorers with 19 for Oklahoma (6-2) which
pulled away in the first half and led easily the rest of the way.

Tasha Crain had 14 points and four assists for the Lady
Techsters (4-4), who were playing their third game in six days.
Shan Moore added 14 points and six rebounds.

Chelsi Welch added 13 points for Oklahoma.

Jackson also had eight assists. It was her third double-double
this season.

Oregon played No. 10 Ohio State in the late game of the Nike
Classic Saturday.
